snippet: Through the years, Rafael Nadal grew accustomed to a couple of givens at the French Open: He would arrive as the defending champion, and Roger Federer would be somewhere in the draw, often awaiting a showdown in the final....
lead_paragraph: Through the years, Rafael Nadal grew accustomed to a couple of givens at the French Open: He would arrive as the defending champion, and Roger Federer would be somewhere in the draw, often awaiting a showdown in the final.

headline.print_headline: Nadal Back in Paris, No Title to Defend, No Federer to Face
headline.main: Nadal Back in Paris, No Title to Defend, No Federer to Face
